descriptions: Vincent van Gogh's 'Starry Night' is a captivating masterpiece that transcends the boundaries of time and space. Painted in 1889 during his stay at the Saint-Paul-de-Mausolea asylum in Saint-Rémy-de-Provence, France, this work is a testament to van Gogh's tumultuous yet profoundly creative inner world.
